                      "ep_id": 4912,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/03/237301566/513d51e0ebfd54f5da34a9f85dfaf61f_4293187669096717509.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Набу Маликата",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Nabu Malikata created Khvarena, who was turned into the divine bird, Simurgh.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4910,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/03/237301566/59da6a8cbcffa112e5d2b63788d7051e_1480677671668697202.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Руккхадевата",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The Greater Lord turned Khvarena into Simurgh so it could guard the forest. The Pari, born from Simurgh, are Rukkhadevata's familiars. Since the information about the Greater Lord was erased from",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "text",
                      "ep_id": 7087,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "name": "Irminsul",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ", the Pari are now considered the familiars of",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "text",
                      "ep_id": 7471,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "name": "Buer",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ".",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4780,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-webstatic.hoyoverse.com/event-static-hoyowiki-admin/2023/12/20/a5b8d23dd3fbe0969cc3ebce78f9c29f_8021351765588020911.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Эгерия",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "After Egeria's death, she became a lake of the pure Amrita. Simurgh drank the Amrita and shattered into millions of pieces. From these pieces, the Pari were born.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Simurgh",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "A divine bird, from whose body the Pari were born.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
